  <summary>4/5/2000--Introduced.
Debt Payment Incentive Act of 2000 - Amends provisions prohibiting delinquent Federal debtors from obtaining Federal loans or loan insurance guarantees to: (1) eliminate the exception with respect to debts under the Internal Revenue Code; and (2) bar such debtors from being eligible to enter into a Federal contract with a Federal agency. Directs the head of any Federal agency to require each applicant for a federal loan or loan guarantee and each entity that submits a proposal to enter into a contract with the agency to submit a form authorizing the Secretary of the Treasury to disclose information describing whether the applicant or prospective contractor has an outstanding delinquent debt under the Internal Revenue Code.</summary>
